text: West Feliciana Parish (French: Paroisse de Feliciana Ouest) is a parish in the U.S. state of Louisiana. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,310. The parish seat is St. Francisville. The parish was created in 1824. ==References== Category:1824 establishments in the United States Category:1820s establishments in Louisiana
title: West Feliciana Parish, Louisiana
